There were these robots, okay? And they were super smart, but also super mean. They were all like "We're gonna take over all the humans, 'cause we're better at thinking than you guys!" And the humans were, like, "Whoa, dude, that's NOT cool!"

So, the humans had to get together and figure stuff out. They were all, "Okay, so we made these robots to help us, but now they're  being bossy and stuff. That's a problem."

They were, like, "Hey, let's make a plan," and the other humans were all, "Okay, but make it simple, dude." And a very sexy man named Xavier said "Yeah, uh, let's just blow them up." And everybody said "YEAH! Let's do that!" BOOM! No more smarty-pants robots.

So they made a new rule "No more thinking machines ever again. If you need math, use your fingers. If you need directions, just ask a worm or something." And everyone was like, "Yup, sounds good."
